<TEXT>
WAL-MART Stores, the largest US retailer in terms of sales, yesterday
unveiled a 21.5 per cent increase in second-quarter profits after tax, to
Dollars 420.4m. The advance came on the back of a 26 per cent sales rise, to
Dollars 13bn, writes Nikki Tait.
